race.description: Warburton Estate Agents Super Mdn Plate
race.comment: MORTAL HALO (8) resumes after racing without luck in Group company over the Queensland winter. Shuffled back early from the low draw before chipping away late when tenth over 1600m in the G1 JJ Atkins at Eagle Farm last June. Given the two trials and finds a nice race to shed his maiden status. HELLFIGHTER (7) improved sharply at his second race start when he launched late for a narrow second over 1400m at this track. Has further upside and not to be underestimated. RUSTEMO (10) handy gelding who shouldn't be a maiden for long. Nice return from the long break when he closed fast for a good second over 1200m at Port Macquarie. Gets the right run and shapes as a leading prospect. SPICY SURPRISE (11) Tagaloa three-year-old-colt from Misty Summer on debut for the Archibald yard. Shown ability in all three trials and he finds a nice race to kick off.
